After spark.streaming.timeout the Spark context will be stopped. This can be done gracefully (waiting for all data to be processed) or immediately.
Note: Used when calling StreamingContext.stop()

Enable Spark checkpointing?
Note: Please see Apache Spark Streaming Guide for more details.

If a checkpoint is found when starting the Spark Streaming application, should the application restart from the checkpoint (e.g.previous failure)? If false, the Spark Streaming application will ignore any existing checkpoints. If true, the Spark Streaming application will restart from an existing checkpoint. If there is no checkpoint, it will start normally.
Reliable directory path for storing Spark checkpoints

Checkpointing requires an HDFS-compatible (reliable) directory for reliably storing checkpoint data. This property defines the base directory. Under this base directory every Spark EU will create a sub-directory with the name of the EU.
Examples:
file:///shared/oracle/checkpoints hdfs://cluster-ns1/user/oracle/spark/checkpoints hdfs://host1.acme.corp:8020/user/oracle/spark/checkpoints
time in seconds, after each period of that, generated RDD will be checkpointed
